Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.45,0:00:09.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kagami Yoshimizu Theater"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.41,0:00:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.87,0:00:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.87,0:00:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grr!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.45,0:00:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit screwing around and start!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.36,0:00:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The ambiguous 3cm? Does that \Nmean it's plushy? Wait!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wrapping is a uniform, \Nargh, it's not an act, pooh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.58,0:00:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotta do your best, gotta just do it{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.29,0:00:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's time to catch 'n' release, eek{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.91,0:00:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Between sweat (whoop) Sweat (whoop){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.95,0:00:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Darlin', darlin', freeze! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.59,0:00:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kinda lethargic, something's kinda comin' out{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.91,0:00:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I love you... Oh wait, one \Nof those was different{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worrywarts, high metal bars {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.12,0:00:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tasty thoughts... And that's enough!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.91,0:00:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heated body of that flying you-know-who{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.70,0:00:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's what you call a normal girlie{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.22,0:00:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Am I the only one surprised? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.62,0:00:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seconds on pork-bone broth \Nramen with wire-hard noodles{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.77,0:00:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Da da da da da {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.94,0:00:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pom-poms cheer squad{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.66,0:00:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's get cherry pie {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happy fun welcoming party {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.01,0:00:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look up! Sensation{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.45,0:00:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah! Feeling of existence, \Ndot dot small planet{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.41,0:00:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Collided and it melted away, in total awe{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.08,0:01:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go all out to sing, shi-ranger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.97,0:01:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Take it away! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.00,0:01:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I should be the one who'll \Nbe laughing in the end{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.50,0:01:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because I have the sailor suit \N← This is my conclusion{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.51,0:01:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's only Monday! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.70,0:01:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Already in a bad mood? What to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.45,0:01:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I really prefer the summer outfits \N← kya! Wah! Good! (cute!) < 3{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.14,0:01:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Until we approach 3 pixels, \Nno hesitations please ★{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.34,0:01:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do your best, be energetic {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.02,0:01:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My darlin', darlin' please! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.37,0:01:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, everyone to your seats!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.97,0:01:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy New Year.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.59,0:01:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, last year just flew by, so \NI'm giving you my best regards.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.95,0:01:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.16,0:01:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for some of you, my regards only \Ngo for about three more months.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.12,0:01:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder who I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.50,0:01:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am! You're not talking about me, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.29,0:01:54.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Delicious Day"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.54,0:01:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can trust you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.51,0:01:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say "a New Year's feeling,"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.29,0:01:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's true that there \Nis a strange atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.91,0:02:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when school starts,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.41,0:02:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the atmosphere changes \Ndrastically, much to my dismay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.45,0:02:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that there's a strange power \Nworking over the New Year's holiday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.79,0:02:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I was so busy helping \Nout at the beginning of the year...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.83,0:02:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gained weight!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.20,0:02:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's the magic of New Year's.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.95,0:02:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it's cold, it's harder \Nfor the fat to burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.75,0:02:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I moved quite a bit too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.33,0:02:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was really busy with shrine maiden \Nstuff for the first days of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.78,0:02:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you ate to make up for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.29,0:02:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shrine maiden New Year's food, \Nshrine maiden rice cake soup,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.87,0:02:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shrine maiden snacks, snacks, snacks, snacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.54,0:02:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shrine maiden snacks... \NSomething along those lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.44,0:02:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, speaking of enjoying \Nthe New Year's holiday...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.04,0:02:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see pictures of {\i1}hanetsuki{\i0}, \Nthe 100 poem card game,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.04,0:02:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and flying kites a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.17,0:02:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I've never seen people \Nreally playing those games.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.00,0:02:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they say that it's dangerous nowadays
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.54,0:02:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because of the power lines \Nand all the traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.41,0:02:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I spent my time watching \NTV and reading books,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.34,0:02:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after the busy first three \Ndays of the year were over.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.31,0:02:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I played them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.04,0:02:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I enjoyed playing {\i1}hanetsuki{\i0}, \Nthe 100 poem card game,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.50,0:02:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and "Fortune's Smile."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.08,0:02:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not how I imagined you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.77,0:03:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that we have a \Nvery westernized house,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.75,0:03:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but our country house is \Nstrictly traditional Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.81,0:03:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the first shrine visit in a kimono,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.37,0:03:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I played together with all of my cousins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.79,0:03:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Even when the gods Held sway in the..."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.58,0:03:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's far more Japanese than me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.37,0:03:16.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More traditional than we are! Or, \Nwhat kind of "Fortune's Smile" face?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.61,0:03:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The 100 poems in the card game \Nare all waka poems, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.34,0:03:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's a game that the \Nplayers pick up the cards with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.37,0:03:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the second half of the poem after \Nthe first half is read out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.83,0:03:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed you can do such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.26,0:03:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm still nowhere close to good...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.62,0:03:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who are really good move quite \Nbriskly, with a nice slap on the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.83,0:03:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's more like...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.33,0:03:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like I'm studying archaic Japanese,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.95,0:03:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I don't like it because it doesn't \Nfeel like I'm playing a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.29,0:03:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those that find intelligent games troublesome
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.25,0:03:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the ones that are ruining Japan's future.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.38,0:03:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, while we're at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.66,0:03:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why can't we have card battles \Nwith the 100 poem cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.66,0:03:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, that monk... Semimaru, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.45,0:03:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Semimaru's shiny-bright attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.49,0:03:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Versus Komachi Ono-no's lovely attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.92,0:03:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going that way again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you played games that move \Nyour body a bit like this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.00,0:03:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe you'd lose at least a little weight?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.66,0:03:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.94,0:04:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because of the rice cakes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.41,0:04:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rice cakes are high in calories.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.11,0:04:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even a piece the size of a matchbox
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.79,0:04:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has basically the same amount of \Nenergy as a small bowl of rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.70,0:04:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means, Kagami was eating \Ngiant bowls of rice each time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.29,0:04:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, didn't you guys eat rice cakes as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.97,0:04:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have a mom at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.37,0:04:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't remember eating much \Nstuff like rice cake soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.61,0:04:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, I don't eat many \Nrice cakes to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.62,0:04:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, what a waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.45,0:04:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rice cake soup, red bean \Nsoup, soy flour mochi...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.66,0:04:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are all sorts of ways \Nto eat delicious rice cakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.03,0:04:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, at this rate, you're going \Nto screw up again next year
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.75,0:04:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the rice cakes, aren't you, Kagamin?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.25,0:04:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does your family eat instead \Nof rice cakes, Izumi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.37,0:04:39.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like, pizza and pasta?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.84,0:04:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our family's year always \Nbegins with fresh pasta!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.17,0:04:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every year, at the end of the year,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.00,0:04:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad washes the pasta machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.91,0:04:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know? If you don't use \Nthat thing for a while, it rusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.95,0:04:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you use it without washing it, \Nit's like, the pasta turns all black.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.33,0:04:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so we clean it up,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.20,0:05:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and make fresh pasta and \Nbake handmade pizza dough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.16,0:05:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds authentic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.75,0:05:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sure that in your house, Kagami,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.54,0:05:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the pizza is delivered and \Nthe pasta is the dried stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.07,0:05:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, we don't eat pizza \Nor pasta for New Year's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.62,0:05:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.68,0:05:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't go well with \Ntraditional New Year's dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.46,0:05:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does too! It's perfect with roast chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.45,0:05:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a New Year's food?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a New Year's food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.95,0:05:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a westernized version \Nof New Year's food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.30,0:05:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.03,0:05:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you guys eat during \NNew Year's, Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.00,0:05:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.22,0:05:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you have the image \Nof a very westernized rich girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.95,0:05:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I bet you don't have rice \Ncakes and New Year's food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.58,0:05:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So do you eat full-course French \Ncuisine on New Year's Day?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.40,0:05:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not really true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.79,0:05:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ate traditional New Year's food,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.62,0:05:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I couldn't bite through the rice cake,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.45,0:05:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I did one of those "stretching \Nout without end" things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.24,0:05:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this walking {\i1}moe {\i0}factor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rice cake, stretching without end...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.16,0:05:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the New Year's vacation \Ngoes by in a rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.20,0:05:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true. Winter vacation \Nends really quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.08,0:05:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It counts as a long break, but \Nyou do the big house cleaning,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:06:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,write New Year's cards, do some homework...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.00,0:06:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, there isn't much time to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.25,0:06:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second! I didn't get \Na New Year's card from you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.38,0:06:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you copied my homework yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.80,0:06:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uguu...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.76,0:06:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0}, did you \Nhave your first dream of the year?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.01,0:06:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... that thing that's said \Nto give you good fortune
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.68,0:06:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you happen to see one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.18,0:06:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, they say one is Fuji, two is hawk,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.52,0:06:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,three is eggplant, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.68,0:06:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that it continues further.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Four is fan, five is tobacco, \Nsix is a lutist monk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.57,0:06:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, so there's up to sixth place...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.61,0:06:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.36,0:06:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those things don't normally \Nshow up in your dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.32,0:06:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of dreams? What's a lutist monk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.41,0:06:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.64,0:06:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you have to see all of them at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.54,0:06:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you saw all of them, that \Nwould be tremendously lucky,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.71,0:06:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I believe any one of them would suffice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.48,0:06:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that you needed to see
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.46,0:06:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,two hawks or three eggplants in your dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.92,0:06:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, to be blunt,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.30,0:06:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember most of the \Ndreams I see in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.72,0:06:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People that really think about that \Nstuff seriously enjoy New Year's.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.31,0:06:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.30,0:06:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My first dream of the year was about
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my shoes being missing when \NI opened my school shoebox.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.52,0:07:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I couldn't do anything about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.19,0:07:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to head home with \Nsomeone else's shoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.32,0:07:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the size wasn't right... \NThat was my dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.61,0:07:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I looked it up in the "Dictionary \Nof Fortune-telling with Dreams,"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.32,0:07:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it said that it meant that \NI was seeking social skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but to gain such skills, it will \Nstill take quite a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.12,0:07:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, shoes in dreams \Nmean social status.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.30,0:07:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheesecake?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.66,0:07:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}... You're quite the ambitious one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.30,0:07:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I kinda get it, but I kinda don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.94,0:07:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard a bunch of people got worked \Nup at their coming-of-age ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.68,0:07:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and went up to the stage, \Nor caused other problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.85,0:07:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't they feel any responsibility, now \Nthat they're part of the face of Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.02,0:07:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why we have to go all \Nthe way out to the ceremony site?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.77,0:07:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.17,0:07:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The coming-of-age ceremony is such \Na pain. I mean, I don't want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.91,0:07:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This girl's on her way to becoming \Na good-for-nothing adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.66,0:07:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami, what are you guys gonna \Nwear to the coming-of-age ceremony?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.54,0:08:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd think since it's a rare occasion, \NI would wear a long-sleeved kimono...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.06,0:08:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since you asked, how about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.79,0:08:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sure Dad will recommend \Nme wearing a long-sleeved kimono.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.84,0:08:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, if it's him...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.26,0:08:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoo-hoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.17,0:08:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.72,0:08:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you wear a long-sleeved kimono,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.84,0:08:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's more of a seven-five-three \Nfestival than coming of age.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.14,0:08:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy New Year! Best regards for this year!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.10,0:08:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Sis, Happy New Year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.44,0:08:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't seen you in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.68,0:08:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, my husband was home, \Nand New Year's is busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.81,0:08:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That, and my younger sister caught a fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.31,0:08:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... That's right, she's very frail.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.07,0:08:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't trying to weasel my way out \Nof giving you New Year's allowance!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.65,0:08:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get me wrong on that, okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.28,0:08:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How the truth comes out, \Nand I didn't even ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.16,0:08:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's what makes her a cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.49,0:08:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a tournament for \Nthe 100 poem card game,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.74,0:08:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it had a great turnout.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.75,0:08:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.23,0:08:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you were a child, Sis,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.67,0:08:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what did you do for play on New Year's Day?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.54,0:08:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.11,0:08:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... I did all sorts \Nof stuff... well... um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:09:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dot... dot... dot... dot...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I forgot. Clean memory wipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.77,0:09:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis really just lives every \Nday in her own groove.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.27,0:09:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I've gotten one \Ndecent conversation out of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.65,0:09:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I blasted all the memories behind me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.36,0:09:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.74,0:09:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, Tsukasa's been cooped \Nup in the {\i1}kotatsu {\i0}all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause it's cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.99,0:09:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know, I know! {\i1}Kotatsu \N{\i0}are wonderful things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.49,0:09:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you have a {\i1}kotatsu{\i0}, even \Ngoing to the bathroom is tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.60,0:09:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.04,0:09:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you shouldn't say stuff \Nlike that so loudly...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.21,0:09:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there is a killer line in our house
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.13,0:09:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that can move people who \Nare cooped up in a {\i1}kotatsu{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.86,0:09:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? How does it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.78,0:09:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konata, if you're planting \Nyourself in the {\i1}kotatsu {\i0}too much,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.26,0:09:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put the {\i1}kotatsu {\i0}away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.25,0:09:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he's fine without a {\i1}kotatsu{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.43,0:09:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He likes it as much as anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.10,0:09:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's just as a lesson to be learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.89,0:09:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, sometimes both of us fall \Nasleep while sitting in a {\i1}kotatsu{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.89,0:09:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I can understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.60,0:09:51.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they say that you'll catch \Na cold sleeping in a {\i1}kotatsu{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.23,0:09:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right. So when I notice it, \NI try to make sure to turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.74,0:09:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, {\i1}kotatsu {\i0}carry heaven \Nand hell together in one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like that when you \Nfirst turn it on as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.16,0:10:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but turned-off {\i1}kotatsu {\i0}seem \Neven colder than necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.12,0:10:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I definitely know how that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.17,0:10:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it tough to get out \Nof the bed in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.51,0:10:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. When you say that,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.04,0:10:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the time between the changing room \Nand the bathtub is really cold too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.42,0:10:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you think twice about \Nrunning around stark naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.13,0:10:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's slippery.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.43,0:10:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That, and don't you hate it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.97,0:10:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you want to go to the \Nbathroom late at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.89,0:10:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, there's that too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.35,0:10:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys, we need to get off the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.22,0:10:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The trip from the bus to \Nthe classroom is also hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.44,0:10:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.78,0:10:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost Valentine's Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.65,0:10:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The air around us gets all \Ncolorful this time of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.27,0:10:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each and every year,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.53,0:10:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the hidden anxiety that \Nshows itself every so often
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.86,0:10:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in everyone acting normally \Nreally tickles me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.03,0:10:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it would be really \Nwonderful if you ask someone out
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.95,0:10:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or get asked out, and your feelings \Nfor each other go through
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.45,0:10:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on days that everyone finds \Nspecial, like this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.83,0:10:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa, you're such a romantic girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.67,0:10:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I'm going to go calling \Nit a candy-company conspiracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.39,0:10:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you say that it's special \Nfor me as well, it might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.09,0:11:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every year, the leftover \Nchocolates get really cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.97,0:11:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The make-your-own chocolate \Nkits are worth aiming for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.18,0:11:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whereas you don't have any dreams at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.51,0:11:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say that you can't buy love!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.56,0:11:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in a way,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.60,0:11:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valentine's Day chocolates are \Na show of love with money.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.10,0:11:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For someone who's only had \Nromances within games,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.23,0:11:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's a pretty harsh thing to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.73,0:11:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in games, getting your \Nimpression points up first
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.44,0:11:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is more important than the actual day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.54,0:11:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For me, there's not much difference \Neven if it's Valentine's Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.99,0:11:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The boys have too many dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.54,0:11:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody was able to trigger \Nthe Kagami flag, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what about you? You have something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.96,0:11:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I'm really popular!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.58,0:11:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, that's in your game, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.00,0:11:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes I seriously \Nworry about your future,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.55,0:11:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with all your talk of flags and \Nimpression points and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.01,0:11:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, what's with only \Ntalking about in-game events?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.64,0:11:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate it when people talk about their \Nbiased opinion when they don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.93,0:11:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, then it's different?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.60,0:11:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, the in-game time for \Nit has been really short,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.52,0:11:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you completely miss \NValentine's Day when playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.81,0:11:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.06,0:12:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this year, I have plans \Nto give chocolate to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.65,0:12:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.90,0:12:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. To someone playing \Nthe same online game as me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.99,0:12:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To one of your gaming buddies?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.45,0:12:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.78,0:12:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me, in person?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.61,0:12:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not like we're physically \Ngoing to see each other or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.24,0:12:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.79,0:12:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to give chocolate to \Nsomeone as a character in-game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, there's another \Nhuman playing it, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.54,0:12:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you really say that it's a real person?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.57,0:12:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, it's just a character in a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.67,0:12:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you talk about my bride that way?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.47,0:12:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Bride?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.47,0:12:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We're married in-game, \Nand I play a male character.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.97,0:12:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. A guy giving \Nchocolate to a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.93,0:12:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, isn't that like a girl \Ngiving one to a girl, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.64,0:12:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the other end is a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.23,0:12:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. My partner \Nis a guy in real life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.98,0:12:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.32,0:12:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, for these things, so long as the \Nones doing it are having fun, it's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.61,0:12:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.91,0:12:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go overseas.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.91,0:12:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's straight out of the blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.99,0:12:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Miyuki-{\i1}san {\i0}said yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.29,0:12:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only in Japan that women give \Nchocolates to men on February 14th.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.50,0:13:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Western countries, people \Ngive candies and cards
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.21,0:13:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to friends and loved ones, \Nregardless of gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.13,0:13:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.76,0:13:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what she said,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.93,0:13:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so even a girl like me would get \Nlots of sweets and stuff, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.26,0:13:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The simplicity of your mind aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.60,0:13:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you really have confidence, \Nin all sorts of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.47,0:13:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was based on the premise \Nthat you're popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.23,0:13:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, it's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.85,0:13:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In foreign countries, smaller girls are--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.10,0:13:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, stop right there! Dangerous \Ncomments are forbidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.57,0:13:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.19,0:13:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy Valentine's Day!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.90,0:13:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0}, this is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.21,0:13:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! Amazing wrapping... is a uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.99,0:13:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing inside too! Heart-shaped!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.99,0:13:31.62,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Happy Valentine's to Kona-{\i1}chan{\i0}"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.62,0:13:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I put a little effort into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.00,0:13:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa gets pretty elaborate \Non things like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.46,0:13:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She made lots and lots of them until morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.00,0:13:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though they're all \Nobligatory chocolates.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.71,0:13:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukasa, obligatory or not, don't \Ngive these things to any guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.13,0:13:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'd all get the wrong idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.84,0:13:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:13:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you can have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.55,0:13:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From Kagami?! For me?! Chocolate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.64,0:13:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Tsukasa was making \Nthem, I just made some too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.14,0:13:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.89,0:13:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Oh!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.14,0:13:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When someone who can do anything \Ndoes something they're not good at,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.73,0:14:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it feels like they put in a tremendous \Neffort behind the scenes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.86,0:14:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Kagami {\i1}moe{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.36,0:14:04.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! Hush, and put it away!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.07,0:14:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.32,0:14:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.40,0:14:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, I'll give this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.45,0:14:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, it's \Nobligatory, okay? Obligatory!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.71,0:14:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me for it having \Nsuch a distorted shape!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.29,0:14:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a fool... What's \Nmore important than shape
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.92,0:14:24.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is the fact that you made it for me, Hiiragi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.71,0:14:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.55,0:14:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot, you idiot, it's not like that at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.72,0:14:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.22,0:14:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. Just shut up and put it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.10,0:14:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never experienced \Nsomething like this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.43,0:14:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The beginning's the most important.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.47,0:14:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you give chocolates \Nto anyone, Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.98,0:14:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave some to my father \Nand to a male relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.23,0:14:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave some to everyone that's \Nfriendly to me every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.57,0:14:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave some to you, Tsukasa, and Miyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.78,0:14:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, everyone had a very \Nboring Saint Valentine's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.90,0:14:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I don't want to hear that from \Nsomeone living in the game world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.27,0:14:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, your cousin \Napplied to Ryouou, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.49,0:14:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she said she got in!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.79,0:14:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since her house is a long way from here,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she'll stay at our place starting next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.58,0:15:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's like a little sister anyway, and \Nour families were talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.00,0:15:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.20,0:15:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But compared to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.55,0:15:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,isn't it hard to tell which \Nof you is the younger sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.63,0:15:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm telling you, she's like a \Nlittle sister, in all sorts of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.26,0:15:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's that small?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.64,0:15:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the fact that she got \Naccepted here smoothly
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.72,0:15:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,means that your cousin must be really smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.60,0:15:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on how you take that line, \Nit sounds a little egotistical.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.39,0:15:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you go here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.31,0:15:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure I just barely made it in!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.61,0:15:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Entrance exams, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.82,0:15:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be going through \Nentrance exams next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.24,0:15:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I guess we'll be immersed \Nin studying all year.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.74,0:15:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.07,0:15:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Entrance exams... Should I take them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.82,0:15:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't thought of my future plans at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.74,0:15:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's better for you to seriously \Nthink about your future, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the words "academic" and "labor" \Ndon't exist in my dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.96,0:15:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of future does that \Nkind of person have in store?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.75,0:15:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A game creator based on hobbies \Nand her actual skills?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.75,0:15:49.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in actuality, it's a \Nhobby in some way or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.51,0:15:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or a manga artist that only \Nmakes money at Comiket?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.37,0:15:52.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Megassa, undara, cheese nyoro-n...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.80,0:15:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe she'll use her \Ncuriosity as a report writer?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.80,0:15:55.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one truth! \NYeah, this has to be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.51,0:15:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about an author whose popularity \Nspikes like the tip of a pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.53,0:15:59.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in this day and age, you \Nhave to go with the light novels!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.52,0:16:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since she's good with computers, \Nmaybe a web designer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.60,0:16:02.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't compromise on this point!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.70,0:16:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or a scriptwriter that uses lots of small \Neveryday events instead of an actual story?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.40,0:16:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or the impossible, moving on to college...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.21,0:16:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, all of them are the same image!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.28,0:16:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.99,0:16:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.34,0:16:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manager! It's Legendary \NGirl A! She's here again!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.21,0:16:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.52,0:16:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We let her slip out of our hands last time...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.63,0:16:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manager!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.38,0:16:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today will be the day
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.84,0:16:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that we will have {\i1}the {\i0}Legendary Girl A
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.13,0:16:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,make it all the way to the \Ngoal named the cash register!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.48,0:16:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Giro.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.54,0:16:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She seems to be indecisive about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.10,0:16:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we should solve her indecision for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.09,0:16:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, everyone, raise \Nyour voices! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.64,0:16:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.10,0:16:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Yeah! Yeah, we say, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.10,0:16:49.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.36,0:16:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manager, I'll go check out Legendary \NGirl A's purchase target for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.82,0:16:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.25,0:16:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,New comics in stock?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! That would be {\i1}Sgt. Frog {\i0}volume 14!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.58,0:17:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Lift up the \Nheight of the flat stacks
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.83,0:17:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that they get in Legendary \NGirl A's line of sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.88,0:17:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And put up a pop-up banner as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.41,0:17:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Equipment complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.59,0:17:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.75,0:17:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Observe her actions for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.67,0:17:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, put all the \Nhot sellers along the path
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.72,0:17:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Legendary Girl A will take \Nfrom there to the cash register!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.34,0:17:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.81,0:17:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manager! The purchase target of \NLegendary Girl A is not a comic!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.73,0:17:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.07,0:17:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manager! Her target has shifted to DVDs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.28,0:17:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Just to be on the safe \Nside, shut off all side corridors,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.36,0:17:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that Legendary Girl A can head \Nstraight to the new release DVD area!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.16,0:17:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.95,0:17:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.58,0:17:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my apologies!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.91,0:17:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tama! Tama!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.18,0:17:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.04,0:17:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tama tama tama tama, tamarincho!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.04,0:17:51.29,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Gero gero gero gero, gemarincho!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.29,0:17:55.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"DVD New Releases"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.63,0:17:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.51,0:18:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manager!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.14,0:18:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, she picked up some merchandise!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.85,0:18:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, I have become victorious today!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.06,0:18:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My comrades, let us drink the \Nsweet wine of victory tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.19,0:18:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.74,0:18:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a feint!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.75,0:18:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This calls for the last resort!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.63,0:18:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now... Bring me that bargain \Nultra-rare out-of-print DVD!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.43,0:18:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manager, she's heading to the cash register.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.68,0:18:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.60,0:18:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is such an emotional scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.27,0:18:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, the entire United States \Nwithin me is cheering and applauding!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.06,0:18:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.90,0:18:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.31,0:18:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That will be 1,785 yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm three yen short.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.33,0:19:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, can you put that back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.26,0:19:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.43,0:19:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.93,0:19:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Channel{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.19,0:19:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning Luckies!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.43,0:19:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we're going to cheerfully \Nbring it to you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.14,0:19:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Times pass by so quickly that {\i1}Lucky \NChannel {\i0}is already on its 13th episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.23,0:19:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, your navigator is your \Nwell-acquainted Akira Kogami!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.96,0:19:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.03,0:19:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I'm Minoru Shiraishi, \Nassistant to Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.90,0:19:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to see all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.66,0:19:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, times pass quickly \Nand we're already on episode 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to enter the second season!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.12,0:19:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How to put it, is it like reaching \Nthe halfway station on Mt. Fuji?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.37,0:19:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.25,0:19:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Mt. Fuji? You can get to \Nthe halfway station by car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.75,0:19:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, that's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:20:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! That's right! I climbed \Nup Mt. Takao for starters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.59,0:20:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Don't you have something \Nto notice before all of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.01,0:20:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.65,0:20:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um, how to say it, your twin \Ndrills are really nice, Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.38,0:20:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is it good? In what way?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.27,0:20:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's all wound up like a seashell...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.98,0:20:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.93,0:20:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well... oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.90,0:20:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.98,0:20:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today we're announcing the results \Nof the special plan we had,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.03,0:20:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the{\i1} Lucky Star {\i0}action figure project!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.90,0:20:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have you, Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}, make \Nthe announcement right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.95,0:20:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the honorable character that will become
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.87,0:20:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an action figure is Miss Konata Izumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.87,0:20:30.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}, please read it properly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.37,0:20:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.09,0:20:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew this would happen. \NWhat is this? A fixed race?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.76,0:20:37.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.76,0:20:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So in the end, the radio and this segment
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.71,0:20:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are less important than the \Nmain show or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.67,0:20:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the case at all, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.97,0:20:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.34,0:20:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, the producer is telling us so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.55,0:20:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, I'll be fooled \Nas many times as you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.68,0:20:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm used to getting betrayed, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.85,0:20:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fooled? That's such a \Ndisgraceful way to put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.10,0:20:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, you haven't had some \Nsort of blueprint in your head
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.56,0:21:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like you'd get yourself made into an \Naction figure or anything, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.23,0:21:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.49,0:21:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the action figure will \Nbe that of Miss Konata Izumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.57,0:21:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, as a booby prize, an action \Nfigure of Minoru Shiraishi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.78,0:21:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.29,0:21:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.79,0:21:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! It's already time for us to say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.71,0:21:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, we ask that you continue \Nto send us your impressions,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.58,0:21:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,encouragement, and opinions \Nabout the program!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.13,0:21:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We accept them on our homepage, \Namong other places!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.46,0:21:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.01,0:21:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.09,0:21:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.32,0:21:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-nee!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.18,0:21:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}, please wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.42,0:21:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, all staff gather around!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.93,0:21:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drill...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.52,0:21:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Clap clap" "Meaningless handclaps"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.64,0:21:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Clap clap" "Meaningless handclaps"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.85,0:21:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Clap clap" "Meaningless handclaps"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.02,0:21:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Clap clap" "Meaningless handclaps"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.56,0:21:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Wa-Wa-Wa... ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.32,0:21:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Wa-Wa-Wawawawawawa... ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.36,0:21:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ S-S-S-Something forgotten ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.84,0:21:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ My, my something I forgot ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.08,0:21:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ That day, that time, I left it behind ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.76,0:22:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ A fragment of a memory ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.79,0:22:00.13,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Snap"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.13,0:22:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ It's all gone ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ With that girl ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.09,0:22:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ The red setting sun is \Nsomehow really bright ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.39,0:22:12.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"He's too rowdy."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.51,0:22:13.72,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Don't make eye contact with him."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.72,0:22:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Jougashima of love ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.64,0:22:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ He's a fool ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.98,0:22:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Laugh at me like that ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.94,0:22:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ That's what is fitting for me ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.29,0:22:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ But... ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.05,0:23:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Once in a while, embrace me gently ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.44,0:23:06.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Next Episode Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.23,0:23:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what's up with the \Nnext episode of {\i1}Sgt. Frog{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.23,0:23:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.44,0:23:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should be the next episode \Nof {\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.24,0:23:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gero gero! I've thought \Nof something wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.56,0:23:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Japanese anime is now a global \Nmotion picture industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.33,0:23:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can use this to brainwash \Nthe people of Pekopon,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.91,0:23:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that will end the conquest \Nof Pekopon in one sweep.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.96,0:23:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sergeant, you're so smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.21,0:23:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How stupid. As a military man,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.04,0:23:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do it like a military man and \Npull it off with military power!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.00,0:23:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet, you red daruma!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.13,0:23:31.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this era, those that seize \Ninformation seize the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.47,0:23:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might not understand that with \Nyour old-fashioned head, Giroro.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.18,0:23:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you, when I let you talk...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.89,0:23:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, the next episode: Under One Roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.89,0:23:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look forward to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.18,0:23:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ge-gero!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.67,0:23:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
